title="Abstract Algebra">Abstract Algebra</fr:link> Section 1.1</fr:meta></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Group</html:dfn> consists of a set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G]]></fr:tex> equipped with an <fr:link
type="local"
href="gr-0003.xml"
addr="gr-0003"
title="Associative binary operator">Associative binary operator</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\star ]]></fr:tex> and an <fr:link
type="local"
href="gr-0005.xml"
addr="gr-0005"
title="Identity element">Identity element</fr:link> with respect to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\star ]]></fr:tex>, usually denoted either <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e\in  G]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[1\in  G]]></fr:tex>, such that every element has a unique <fr:link
type="local"
href="gr-000C.xml"
addr="gr-000C"
title="Inverse of an element with respect to a binary operator">inverse</fr:link>,
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\forall  a\in  G\ldotp \exists  a^{-1}\in  A\ldotp  a\star  a^{-1}=a^{-1}\star  a=e.]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
 
   
